    {
      "text": "Kid's Horehore Daisakusen is a 1987 action video game developed and published by Nichibutsu for arcades. A port for the Family Computer was released under the name Booby Kids. A port to the TurboGrafx-16 developed by Hudson Soft was released as Cratermaze, which was released outside Japan unlike the other versions.\nA sequel named Booby Boys was released by Nichibutsu for the Game Boy in 1993.",
